    <fr:title text="Terminal coalgebra">Terminal coalgebra</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Fix an endofunctor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F : \mathcal {C} \to  \mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex>. A <html:em>terminal
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>-coalgebra</html:em>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\nu  F]]></fr:tex>, is a terminal object of the
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F9/" title="Coalgebras as a displayed category" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F9/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F9/" type="local">category of coalgebras</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Coalg}{\mathopen {}\left (F\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> — equivalently, an
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F8/" title="Initial algebra" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F8/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F8/" type="local">initial algebra</fr:link> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F^{\mathrm {op}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
    <html:p>Unfolding the universal property: a terminal coalgebra is a coalgebra
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\nu  F, \mathrm {out}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> such that every coalgebra <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (x, \gamma \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>
admits a unique morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {unfold}\;\gamma  : x \to  \nu  F]]></fr:tex>
satisfying
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mathrm {unfold}\;\gamma \right )\mathclose {}} \star  \mathrm {out}
   = \gamma  \star  F{\mathopen {}\left (\mathrm {unfold}\;\gamma \right )\mathclose {}}.]]></fr:tex></html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
