            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F8/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Initial algebra">Initial algebra</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Fix an endofunctor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F : \mathcal {C} \to  \mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex>. An <html:em>initial
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>-algebra</html:em>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu  F]]></fr:tex>, is an initial object of the
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F7/" title="Algebras as a displayed category" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F7/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00F7/" type="local">category of algebras</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Alg}{\mathopen {}\left (F\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>Unfolding the universal property: an initial algebra is an algebra
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mu  F, \mathrm {in}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> such that every algebra <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (x, \alpha \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>
admits a unique morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {fold}\;\alpha  : \mu  F \to  x]]></fr:tex>
satisfying
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathrm {in} \star  {\mathopen {}\left (\mathrm {fold}\;\alpha \right )\mathclose {}}
   = F{\mathopen {}\left (\mathrm {fold}\;\alpha \right )\mathclose {}} \star  \alpha .]]></fr:tex></html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
